'''剝蝕節理'''（英语：exfoliation joint或sheet joints）是一種在岩石表面平行的結構，常常導致對岩石內部的進一步侵蝕。

== 地質特點 ==

* 通常遵循地形<ref name="Gilbert1904">{{Cite journal|title=Domes and dome structures of the high Sierra|last=Gilbert|first=G.K.|journal=Bulletin of the Geological Society of America|year=1904|volume=15|pages=29–36|author-link=Grove Karl Gilbert}}</ref><ref name="Matthes1930">{{Cite journal|title=Geologic history of the Yosemite Valley|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=elVYAAAAMAAJ|last=Matthes|first=F.E.|journal=U.S. Geological Survey Professional|year=1930|volume=160|author-link=François E. Matthes|access-date=2020-12-06|archive-date=2014-01-01|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140101050351/http://books.google.com/books?id=elVYAAAAMAAJ|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name="Goodman1993">{{Cite book|last=Goodman|first=R.E.|year=1993|title=Engineering Geology|publisher=John Wiley and Sons|location=New York}}</ref>。
* 將岩石分解為副平面<ref name="Goodman1993">{{Cite book|last=Goodman|first=R.E.|year=1993|title=Engineering Geology|publisher=John Wiley and Sons|location=New York}}</ref>。
* 節理的間距隨著深度從表面附近的幾厘米增加到深處的幾米<ref name="Goodman19933">{{Cite book|last=Goodman|first=R.E.|year=1993|title=Engineering Geology|publisher=John Wiley and Sons|location=New York}}</ref><ref name="Dale19232">{{Cite journal|title=The commercial granites of New England|url=https://archive.org/details/commercialgranit00dale|last=Dale|first=T.N.|journal=United States Geological Survey Bulletin|year=1923|volume=738}}</ref><ref name="Jahns19432">{{Cite journal|title=Sheet structures in granites|last=Jahns|first=R.H.|journal=Journal of Geology|issue=2|doi=10.1086/625130|year=1943|volume=51|pages=71–98|bibcode=1943JG.....51...71J}}</ref>。
* 目前已知最大的剝蝕節理深度約為100米<ref name="Goodman19932">{{Cite book|last=Goodman|first=R.E.|year=1993|title=Engineering Geology|publisher=John Wiley and Sons|location=New York}}</ref><ref name="Dale1923">{{Cite journal|title=The commercial granites of New England|url=https://archive.org/details/commercialgranit00dale|last=Dale|first=T.N.|journal=United States Geological Survey Bulletin|year=1923|volume=738}}</ref><ref name="Jahns1943">{{Cite journal|title=Sheet structures in granites|last=Jahns|first=R.H.|journal=Journal of Geology|issue=2|doi=10.1086/625130|year=1943|volume=51|pages=71–98|bibcode=1943JG.....51...71J}}</ref><ref name="Holzhausen1989">{{Cite journal|title=Origin of sheet structure, 1. Morphology and boundary conditions|last=Holzhausen|first=G.R.|journal=Engineering Geology|issue=1–4|doi=10.1016/0013-7952(89)90035-5|year=1989|volume=27|pages=225–278}}</ref>。
* 節理的縫隙是可拉伸的<ref name="Bahatetal1999">{{Cite journal|title=Mechanism of exfoliation joint formation in granitic rocks, Yosemite National Park|first1=D.|last2=Grossenbacher|first2=K.|date=January 1999|journal=Journal of Structural Geology|issue=1|doi=10.1016/s0191-8141(98)00069-8|volume=21|pages=85–96|bibcode=1999JSG....21...85B|issn=0191-8141|last3=Karasaki|first3=K.|last1=Bahat}}</ref><ref name="mandl2005">{{Cite book|last=Mandl|first=G.|year=2005|title=Rock Joints|publisher=Springer-Verlag|location=Berlin|isbn=9783642063916}}</ref>。
* 發生在許多不同的岩性和氣候帶中，並非冰川景觀獨有<ref name="Goodman19934">{{Cite book|last=Goodman|first=R.E.|year=1993|title=Engineering Geology|publisher=John Wiley and Sons|location=New York}}</ref><ref name="Bradley1963">{{Cite journal|title=Large-scale exfoliation in massive sandstones of the Colorado Plateau|last=Bradley|first=W.C.|journal=Geological Society of America Bulletin|issue=5|doi=10.1130/0016-7606(1963)74[519:LEIMSO]2.0.CO;2|year=1963|volume=74|pages=519–527}}</ref><ref name="Twidale1973">{{Cite journal|title=On the origin of sheet jointing|last=Twidale|first=C.R.|journal=Rock Mechanics and Rock Engineering|issue=3|doi=10.1007/BF01238046|year=1973|volume=5|pages=163–187|bibcode=1973RMFMR...5..163T|author-link=Charles Rowland Twidale}}</ref>。
* 基岩通常是稀疏節理的，各向同性的，並且具有很高的抗壓強度。
*可以具有或凹或凸的向上彎曲<ref name="Gilbert19042">{{Cite journal|title=Domes and dome structures of the high Sierra|last=Gilbert|first=G.K.|journal=Bulletin of the Geological Society of America|year=1904|volume=15|pages=29–36|author-link=Grove Karl Gilbert}}</ref><ref name="Matthes19302">{{Cite journal|title=Geologic history of the Yosemite Valley|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=elVYAAAAMAAJ|last=Matthes|first=F.E.|journal=U.S. Geological Survey Professional|year=1930|volume=160|author-link=François E. Matthes|access-date=2020-12-06|archive-date=2014-01-01|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140101050351/http://books.google.com/books?id=elVYAAAAMAAJ|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name="RomaniTwidale1999">{{Cite journal|title=Sheet fractures, other stress forms and some engineering implications|first1=J.R.|last2=Twidale|first2=C.R.|journal=Geomorphology|doi=10.1016/S0169-555X(99)00070-7|year=1999|volume=31|pages=13–27|bibcode=1999Geomo..31...13V|last1=Romani}}</ref>。
* 通常與其他次生地質活動相聯繫，例如拱起、彎曲<ref name="RomaniTwidale19992">{{Cite journal|title=Sheet fractures, other stress forms and some engineering implications|first1=J.R.|last2=Twidale|first2=C.R.|journal=Geomorphology|doi=10.1016/S0169-555X(99)00070-7|year=1999|volume=31|pages=13–27|bibcode=1999Geomo..31...13V|last1=Romani}}</ref>。

